      "content": "The thought that leaving would be the ultimate act of love is a terrifying one, but it is also a very common belief among parents who feel they have failed. It is worth noting that while you cannot control your children's future, you can control your presence, and staying to face the reality of your mistakes is often more powerful than disappearing. If you feel like you are dragging them down, perhaps it is time to seek professional help to figure out how to navigate this difficult path forward.",
